00:21:27,720 --> 00:21:30,530
Yesterday, I met the Hospital Director.

292
00:21:30,530 --> 00:21:31,720
Did you talk to her about it?

293
00:21:31,720 --> 00:21:35,530
She tried to persuade me to help her, actually.

294
00:21:35,530 --> 00:21:38,120
She's very determined, unlike before.

295
00:21:38,120 --> 00:21:41,190
You said the two of you were classmates in high school right?

296
00:21:41,190 --> 00:21:43,660
What kind of person is the Hospital Director?

297
00:21:44,720 --> 00:21:47,210
Before, she had a strong sense of justice.

298
00:21:47,210 --> 00:21:48,930
Then there's no reason she wouldn't understand.

299
00:21:48,930 --> 00:21:50,830
Right?

300
00:21:54,490 --> 00:21:56,470
- How are you? 
 - With what?

301
00:21:56,470 --> 00:22:01,170
Aren't you depressed at all? You can't respond to something like this like others.

302
00:22:01,170 --> 00:22:03,960
For some reason, I'm not depressed.

303
00:22:03,960 --> 00:22:07,900
At any other time, if I heard news like this, I would hit rock bottom

304
00:22:07,900 --> 00:22:10,820
and walk multiple laps around the trails.

305
00:22:10,820 --> 00:22:12,490
Are you sure?

306
00:22:12,490 --> 00:22:15,210
Why would I hide that?

307
00:22:17,230 --> 00:22:22,080
If Han Woo Joo is going to continue with consultations,

308
00:22:22,080 --> 00:22:25,920
change her appointment time to a less busy time.

309
00:22:25,920 --> 00:22:27,260
Do I have to go to such lengths?

310
00:22:27,260 --> 00:22:30,450
Nothing good will come of it if the Hospital Director finds out.

311
00:22:30,450 --> 00:22:33,260
Let's live a little quietly.

312
00:22:34,520 --> 00:22:36,660
Okay.

313
00:22:42,680 --> 00:22:46,200
Sometimes, I think about when we were residents.

314
00:22:46,200 --> 00:22:49,080
When? First year?

315
00:22:49,080 --> 00:22:54,280
You mean when we didn't know how to do a single thing and was dragged everywhere by our patients?

316
00:22:54,280 --> 00:22:55,690
Yeah.

317
00:22:55,690 --> 00:22:58,310
Ji Young Won was especially bad.

318
00:22:58,310 --> 00:23:00,510
- Me? 
 - Don't you remember? Who was that?

319
00:23:00,510 --> 00:23:04,100
I think he might've been a pastor? The patient who heard things.

320
00:23:04,100 --> 00:23:06,540
- You mean the patient who had dissociation disorder? 
 - Yea, that one.

321
00:23:06,540 --> 00:23:10,780
Every time Young Won had a consultation with that patient, she was caught there for 10 hours.

322
00:23:10,780 --> 00:23:16,350
She listened to everything he said, without interrupting him to even go to the bathroom.

323
00:23:17,660 --> 00:23:20,290
How did you know that?

324
00:23:20,290 --> 00:23:24,860
Right, she was the one that was most swayed by the patient's mood.

325
00:23:24,860 --> 00:23:28,140
If the patient laughed, she laughed. If the patient cried, she cried.

326
00:23:28,140 --> 00:23:31,060
You were worse than me on that one!

327
00:23:31,060 --> 00:23:33,560
I think Young Won had the most difficulty in the ER.

328
00:23:33,560 --> 00:23:36,990
That's right. When I had the night shift in the ER, I almost passed out.

329
00:23:36,990 --> 00:23:40,790
Why? I loved the ER the most. I still do.

330
00:23:40,790 --> 00:23:44,800
Young Won had such a difficult time with all the ER patients.

331
00:23:44,800 --> 00:23:49,060
She's yelled at a patient before, asking if they were planning on dying? Right?

332
00:23:49,060 --> 00:23:51,550
Why do you remember all those things?

333
00:23:53,200 --> 00:23:55,940
I know, right?

334
00:23:55,940 --> 00:23:58,850
Well, everyone has things they can't forget.

335
00:23:58,850 --> 00:24:01,280
What do you remember?

336
00:24:07,730 --> 00:24:13,610
The day I first saw symptoms of abnormality in my father.

337
00:24:13,610 --> 00:24:20,040
And my mom's face the day they got a divorce.

338
00:24:22,470 --> 00:24:25,910
For me, it's Nurse Heo's text.

339
00:24:25,910 --> 00:24:28,140
Never mind. I'll leave first.

340
00:24:28,140 --> 00:24:29,190
Why?

341
00:24:29,190 --> 00:24:31,690
I have something to tell Nurse Heo's mom.

342
00:24:31,690 --> 00:24:34,200
Do it later. If you go now, you'll only get in trouble.

343
00:24:34,200 --> 00:24:36,500
I'm still going to go.

344
00:24:40,900 --> 00:24:42,560
I think I should go with her.

345
00:24:42,560 --> 00:24:44,390
Take care of this.

346
00:25:03,160 --> 00:25:04,990
I'll go with you.

347
00:25:11,450 --> 00:25:15,460

348
00:25:25,190 --> 00:25:26,510
Woo Joo.

349
00:25:26,510 --> 00:25:29,840
I just thought of a piece,

350
00:25:29,840 --> 00:25:31,720
give it a listen.

351
00:25:43,400 --> 00:25:45,220
What do you think?

352
00:25:53,300 --> 00:25:55,030
- I've found the one. 
 - This one?

353
00:25:55,030 --> 00:25:56,520
- We've found it! 
 - We found it.

354
00:25:56,520 --> 00:26:01,840
But we can't use this exactly song. I'll edit it, so you change the lyrics.

355
00:26:01,840 --> 00:26:06,170
Me?

356
00:26:06,170 --> 00:26:07,540
I'll try it!

357
00:26:07,540 --> 00:26:11,030
- This one, okay? 
 - Wait a  minute.

358
00:26:13,450 --> 00:26:15,390
Hello?

359
00:26:16,420 --> 00:26:18,960
Where are you? Where, where?

360
00:26:20,450 --> 00:26:22,870
Okay I'll be right there!

361
00:26:23,730 --> 00:26:26,530
I'm heading out!

362
00:26:26,530 --> 00:26:27,790
Bye!

363
00:26:27,790 --> 00:26:31,660
Goodness... do you like him that much?

364
00:26:32,860 --> 00:26:35,420
Yes, I do.

365
00:26:46,020 --> 00:26:50,990
Dr. Noh! I put the sign up that we're closed.

366
00:26:50,990 --> 00:26:54,720
I came in because I saw that. You're closing down and heading home right?

367
00:26:54,720 --> 00:26:56,150
Let's head out together.

368
00:26:56,150 --> 00:26:57,210
To where?

369
00:26:57,210 --> 00:27:01,460
Anywhere. The weather is nice.

370
00:27:01,460 --> 00:27:03,120
Deal!

371
00:27:22,880 --> 00:27:25,670
Oh, I did it again by accident!

372
00:27:25,670 --> 00:27:28,420
Well, I don't think anyone really cares.

373
00:27:28,420 --> 00:27:30,860
I'm not falling for that anymore.

374
00:27:30,860 --> 00:27:35,590
Right? If you fell for that three times, you'd be a dummy.

375
00:27:53,750 --> 00:27:56,790
 The person you are trying to call...

376
00:27:56,790 --> 00:27:59,230
She's not picking up.

377
00:27:59,230 --> 00:28:02,200
Let's just leave today and come back tomorrow.

378
00:28:02,200 --> 00:28:03,980
Okay.

379
00:28:17,340 --> 00:28:20,580
I came because I had something to tell you.

380
00:28:20,580 --> 00:28:24,550
It's not about me, but Nurse Heo.

381
00:28:24,550 --> 00:28:28,170
There's something Nurse Heo used to tell me during our consultations.

382
00:28:28,170 --> 00:28:31,750
I thought it was something you should know.

383
00:28:33,050 --> 00:28:37,520
Just tell me what you need to say and leave.

384
00:28:37,520 --> 00:28:40,460
Nurse Heo told me

385
00:28:41,330 --> 00:28:47,920
that when you left her at her father's house after your divorce,

386
00:28:47,920 --> 00:28:51,590
she didn't think you had just tossed her away.

387
00:28:52,530 --> 00:29:00,460
She said she couldn't think that...

388
00:29:00,460 --> 00:29:03,130
because of how many times you turned around as you left.

389
00:29:04,530 --> 00:29:09,950
So when she met you again after she turned 20,

390
00:29:09,950 --> 00:29:12,840
she was really happy and glad.

391
00:29:14,880 --> 00:29:18,360
She wanted to go to famous restaurants and travel with you.

392
00:29:18,360 --> 00:29:25,540
There are so many things she wanted to do with you, but she wasn't sure if she could because your relationship was awkward.

393
00:29:25,540 --> 00:29:31,260
She thought her mother felt too guilty about leaving her.

394
00:29:32,260 --> 00:29:36,090
Min Young's biggest worry was about

395
00:29:36,090 --> 00:29:39,760
how she could best get close to you.

396
00:29:39,760 --> 00:29:45,670
Even when she went to eat with me,

397
00:29:47,040 --> 00:29:49,230
she kept saying she'd better come here with her mother.

398
00:30:20,500 --> 00:30:24,250
 Depression is not just a state of being sad.

399
00:30:24,250 --> 00:30:30,650
 It's an empty state of your mind being empty and your body being paralyzed.

400
00:30:30,650 --> 00:30:36,650
 You're in a state of despair, without energy or the strength to do anything.

